<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-16-1432 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper evaluates a zirconium dioxide refractory, containing calciumoxide as a stabilizing agent, for its use and performance as a candidatethermal insulation material in gas-fired furnaces for the melting ofsilica. Properties for which tests are conducted include heat resistance,ultimate compressive strength, porosity, bulk density, corrosion anderosion resistance, and its potential for interacting with molten silica.</TEXT></DOC>